11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 11 O.S. 2021, Section 21-110, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 21-110. A. Territory may be detached from the
15 corporate limits of a municipality by the governing body when:
16 1. An ordinance of the governing body so directs; or
17 2. A petition requesting detachment, signed by at least three-
18 fourths (3/4) of the registered voters and by the owners of at least
19 three-fourths (3/4), in value, of the property to be detached, is
20 filed with the governing body.
21 Only land which is within the limits of the municipality and
22 upon its border and not laid out in lots and blocks, or land which
23 had been annexed to a municipality, may be detached by petition.
